He
shrunk
still
further
away
as
I
spoke,
and
I
could
see
on
his
face
that
he
thought
I
was
mad.
So
I
was
for
the
time.
The
pulses
in
my
temples
beat
like
sledge
hammers,
and
I
believe
I
would
have
had
a
fit
of
some
sort
