"'What
do
you
think
of
Lucy
Ferrier
now?'
I
cried,
locking
the
door,
and
shaking
the
key
in
his
face.
'Punishment
has
been
slow
in
coming,
but
it
has
overtaken
you
at
last.'
I
saw
his
coward
lips
tremble
as
I
spoke.
He
would
have
begged
for
his
life,
but
he
knew
well
that
it
was
useless.
"'Would
you
murder
me?'
he
